  <refnamediv>
	<refname>lod_resolve</refname>
	<refpurpose>Resolve a Linked Open Data URI</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  
  <refsynopsisdiv>
	<funcsynopsis>
	  <funcsynopsisinfo>#include &lt;liblod.h&gt;</funcsynopsisinfo>
	  <funcprototype>
		<funcdef>LODINSTANCE * <function>lod_resolve</function></funcdef>
		<paramdef>LODCONTEXT *<parameter>context</parameter></paramdef>
		<paramdef>const char *<parameter>uri</parameter></paramdef>
		<paramdef>LODFETCH <parameter>mode</parameter></paramdef>
	  </funcprototype>
	</funcsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1>
	<title>Description</title>
	
	<para>
	  <function>lod_resolve</function> attempts to
	  <firstterm>resolve</firstterm> a Linked Open Data URI: that is,
	  perform one or more HTTP requests in order to obtain data describing
	  the subject identified by <parameter>uri</parameter>.
	</para>
	
	<para>
	  The behaviour of <function>lod_resolve</function> depends upon the
	  value of the <parameter>mode</parameter> parameter:
	</para>
	
	<variablelist>
	  <varlistentry>
		<term><constant>FETCH_NEVER</constant></term>
		<listitem>
		  <para>
			Do not perform any network (HTTP) requests. If the subject
			identified by <parameter>uri</parameter> already exists in
			the model, the returned instance will reference it.
		  </para>
		</listitem>
	  </varlistentry>

	  <varlistentry>
		<term><constant>FETCH_ALWAYS</constant></term>
		<listitem>
		  <para>
			Resolve the URI by performing network (HTTP) requests, even if
			triples whose subject is the supplied <parameter>uri</parameter>
			already exist in the model.
		  </para>
		</listitem>
	  </varlistentry>

	  <varlistentry>
		<term><constant>FETCH_ABSENT</constant></term>
		<listitem>
		  <para>
			If triples whose subject is the supplied
			<parameter>uri</parameter>, simply return a
			<type>LODINSTANCE</type> referring to those triples. Otherwise,
			attempt to perform network (HTTP) requests to obtain data
			describing the subject (as with <constant>FETCH_ALWAYS</constant>).
		  </para>
		</listitem>
	  </varlistentry>
	</variablelist>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
	<title>Return value</title>

	<para>
	  Upon success, <function>lod_resolve</function> returns a new
	  <type>LODINSTANCE</type>, which should be later freed using
	  <function>lod_instance_destroy</function>.
	</para>

	<para>
	  If an error occurs, <function>lod_resolve</function> returns
	  <constant>NULL</constant>. A description of the error condition
	  can be obtained using <function>lod_errmsg</function>.
	</para>
  </refsect1>

